Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows hypoglycemia with low HbA1c, elevated creatinine, metabolic acidosis (low CO₂), and significant proteinuria, glycosuria, and ketonuria. Urine is cloudy, brown, and has low specific gravity. These findings suggest possible advanced renal dysfunction, poor glycemic control (possibly malnutrition or insulin overuse), and possible dehydration or catabolic state. Urinary findings may also indicate underlying urinary tract pathology. Clinical correlation and further evaluation are recommended.
